The president of a Krasnoyarsk court had his ID stolen after being hit on the head
Unknown persons attacked the president of the Krasnoyarsk regional court Vladimir Dvoekonko, stealing his ID.
As Interfax reports, late Wednesday evening the perpetrators hit the judge on the head, from which he lost consciousness.
When the 63-year-old president of the court regained consciousness, he discovered that they had stolen his work ID.
The perpetrators did not take money or other valuables.
Dvoekonko made it home by himself but contacted police only on the following day.
A criminal investigation and search for the perpetrators is being conducted.
